data.content:
Three breaking changes affect your code. Here's each one and the fix:

---

### 1. `ExecuteUpdateAsync` — no longer accepts expression trees

The setter parameter changed from `Expression<Func<...>>` to `Func<...>`. Your manual expression tree code **won't compile**. Replace it with a simple lambda:

```csharp
await context.Blogs.ExecuteUpdateAsync(s =>
{
    s.SetProperty(b => b.Views, 8);
    if (nameChanged)
    {
        s.SetProperty(b => b.Name, "foo");
    }
});
```

---

### 2. Complex type columns — two changes

**a) Duplicate column names are now uniquified.** If `ShippingAddress.Street` and `BillingAddress.Street` previously shared one column, EF 10 appends a number (e.g. `Street1`). To preserve the old shared-column behavior, pin names explicitly:

```csharp
b.ComplexProperty(c => c.ShippingAddress, p =>
    p.Property(a => a.Street).HasColumnName("Street"));
b.ComplexProperty(c => c.BillingAddress, p =>
    p.Property(a => a.Street).HasColumnName("Street"));
```

**b) Nested complex types now use the full path** for column names. `Order.Payment.BillingAddress.City` was `BillingAddress_City`, now becomes `Payment_BillingAddress_City`. To keep old names:

```csharp
modelBuilder.Entity<Order>()
    .ComplexProperty(o => o.Payment)
    .ComplexProperty(p => p.BillingAddress)
    .Property(a => a.City)
    .HasColumnName("BillingAddress_City");
```

Both changes generate new migrations — review them carefully to avoid data loss.

---

### 3. `IRelationalCommandDiagnosticsLogger` — new `logCommandText` parameter

All methods (`CommandReaderExecuting`, `CommandReaderExecuted`, etc.) now require an additional `string logCommandText` parameter. This carries redacted SQL (constants scrubbed unless `EnableSensitiveDataLogging` is on):

```csharp
public InterceptionResult<DbDataReader> CommandReaderExecuting(
    IRelationalConnection connection,
    DbCommand command,
    DbContext context,
    Guid commandId,
    Guid connectionId,
    DateTimeOffset startTime,
    string logCommandText)   // ← add this
{
    // Use logCommandText for logging (redacted)
    // Use command.CommandText for actual SQL
}
```

Update **every** method on your `MyLogger` class — they all gained this parameter.
